metadata.name: Out Of Eden
metadata.description:
I'm sorry but calling you a goddess would be an insult to your name pretty lady.
The gods are perfectly flawed beings that punish and destroy when they are not showed love...
You are far greater than that love...
Tonight as the stars shines bright,
I set sail to the great beyond in search for a title you can call your own,
One that has never been heard by the ears of man 
nor the ears of angels above nor the gods themselves.
